# mjbots Libraries

## Purpose

This folder contains local copies of the `moteus` and `pi3hat` libraries from the mjbots project. Rather than relying on the upstream packages directly, these libraries have been vendored into this repository to give us full version control over the exact code we depend on.

The motivation is straightforward: upstream mjbots libraries can and do change. New releases may introduce API changes, behavioural differences, or bugs that would silently break our current working system if we pulled the latest versions automatically. By keeping a known-good copy here, we control exactly when (and whether) to update, and any changes can be reviewed and tested deliberately rather than being forced on us.

## How It Was Built

The libraries were not modified or re-implemented. They are a direct copy-paste from the official mjbots repositories, taken from the `lib/cpp/moteus` and `lib/cpp/pi3hat` subdirectories respectively. This keeps the code identical to the upstream version we validated against, while still isolating us from future upstream changes.

on the pi3hat.h we have made a modifaction to enable_aux = false this was to adress an aux error. 
